Here's a thorough analysis of the Express application covering OWASP Top 10 and common Node.js vulnerabilities.

---

## 🔴 Critical Issues

### 1. No Body Parser / Input Validation Middleware
The app has no body parsing middleware, which means if you add POST/PUT routes later, there's no foundation for input validation.

```js
// MISSING: Body parsing with size limits
app.use(express.json({ limit: '1kb' }));  // Restrict payload size
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '1kb' }));
```

### 2. No Helmet (Missing Security Headers)
